very useful, especially Downloads if you do file downloads from the internet.

17
00:00:57.405 --> 00:00:59.528
On the right-hand side of the taskbar,

18
00:00:59.528 --> 00:01:01.652
we have what's called the Notification area.

19
00:01:01.652 --> 00:01:06.044
This can get kind of cluttered, but of course, you can customize how it behaves.

20
00:01:06.044 --> 00:01:08.096
You'll notice that my taskbar may look a little

21
00:01:08.096 --> 00:01:09.995
different from how you have yours setup.

22
00:01:09.995 --> 00:01:11.969
I have some things turned off.

23
00:01:11.969 --> 00:01:16.407
If we right-click an empty area of the taskbar and come up to Task View button,

24
00:01:16.407 --> 00:01:18.423
this is something that you might have.

25
00:01:18.423 --> 00:01:22.491
Task View is a way to work with multiple open windows.

26
00:01:22.491 --> 00:01:24.236
When you click Task View,

27
00:01:24.236 --> 00:01:28.742
you get a nice tiled collection of windows that are open on that

28
00:01:28.742 --> 00:01:31.139
system and these could be application instances,

29
00:01:31.139 --> 00:01:34.661
like you see here, I have PowerShell and I have Microsoft Edge,

30
00:01:34.661 --> 00:01:37.867
and then I can left-click the one that I want to bring to the foreground.

31
00:01:37.867 --> 00:01:41.167
There are other cool things you can do like snap windows.

32
00:01:41.167 --> 00:01:42.824
Do you see what I did there?

33
00:01:42.824 --> 00:01:45.927
This is using the mouse and left-click and left dragging the

34
00:01:45.927 --> 00:01:49.184
window to a border and you see that halo,

35
00:01:49.184 --> 00:01:52.075
that means it's going to wrap that window to the halfway

36
00:01:52.075 --> 00:01:55.507
point and then any other open windows will show up as tiles

37
00:01:55.507 --> 00:01:57.260
and this provides a nice interface,

38
00:01:57.260 --> 00:02:00.507
a nice way when I'm doing a lot of file copying,

39
00:02:00.507 --> 00:02:01.008
for instance,

40
00:02:01.008 --> 00:02:03.765
I may have two instances of File Explorer open and I

41
00:02:03.765 --> 00:02:05.507
may want to tile them this way.

42
00:02:05.507 --> 00:02:07.496
You can also do other kinds of tiles.

43
00:02:07.496 --> 00:02:10.706
If you go to the top, that'll do a maximize.

44
00:02:10.706 --> 00:02:13.240
If you go to the bottom, it doesn't look like it does anything,

45
00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:15.416
but at least it goes to the left or right.

46
00:02:15.416 --> 00:02:18.440
In the corners, this is a power user tip right here.

47
00:02:18.440 --> 00:02:22.874
The corner allows you to tile up to four Windows, which is pretty convenient.

48
00:02:22.874 --> 00:02:25.667
Now I could do a third one down in the lower left,

49
00:02:25.667 --> 00:02:28.005
or potentially, I could have four tiled windows.

50
00:02:28.005 --> 00:02:31.506
Those are features that are enabled by default and overridable

51
00:02:31.506 --> 00:02:34.355
by visiting settings as you would imagine.

52
00:02:34.355 --> 00:02:35.870
Now I have a bunch of icons.

53
00:02:35.870 --> 00:02:38.298
We don't need to describe what each one does here,

54
00:02:38.298 --> 00:02:41.430
but if you right-click each one of those icons,

55
00:02:41.430 --> 00:02:44.772
you're going to get a jump list, at least for most of them,

56
00:02:44.772 --> 00:02:45.596
with different options.

