In this case, if I double left-click the One Drive,

64
00:03:08.704 --> 00:03:12.517
it shows me from my Microsoft account, my One Drive folders.

65
00:03:12.517 --> 00:03:16.616
Over on the very right, we have the notification system, which is super cool.

66
00:03:16.616 --> 00:03:19.623
By default, any apps that have something to tell you,

67
00:03:19.623 --> 00:03:22.452
your email program letting you know you have a new message,

68
00:03:22.452 --> 00:03:25.342
your calendar app letting you know you have an upcoming appointment,

69
00:03:25.342 --> 00:03:28.149
these will show up in your notifications list.

70
00:03:28.149 --> 00:03:30.080
So I really love this feature myself.

71
00:03:30.080 --> 00:03:31.183
When you left-click it,

72
00:03:31.183 --> 00:03:34.323
besides seeing notifications that you can always dismiss by

73
00:03:34.323 --> 00:03:36.176
clicking the close icon that will appear,

74
00:03:36.176 --> 00:03:38.656
you'll see down below we can get to, again,

75
00:03:38.656 --> 00:03:40.554
some really handy options.

76
00:03:40.554 --> 00:03:43.633
Quiet hours, for instance, will suppress notifications.

77
00:03:43.633 --> 00:03:46.220
When I'm recording these modules, for instance,

78
00:03:46.220 --> 00:03:48.994
I have my notification center snoozing because I don't

79
00:03:48.994 --> 00:03:50.670
want to be interrupted while I work.

80
00:03:50.670 --> 00:03:53.557
We can get to our network connections really easily

81
00:03:53.557 --> 00:03:56.459
and browse different networks, really handy,

82
00:03:56.459 --> 00:03:57.420
especially all settings,

83
